[
    {
        "content": "<p>What it says in the topic. Zulip allows custom emojis, we (presumably mods) can upload gifs by going Manage Organisation -&gt; custom emoji. We currently do not have any, and this state of affairs is terrible</p>",
        "id": 217417656,
        "sender_full_name": "Jules Hedges",
        "timestamp": 1605887214
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Clearly at an <em>absolute minimum</em> we need the picture of Grothendieck with glowing eyes as an emoji</p>",
        "id": 217417744,
        "sender_full_name": "Jules Hedges",
        "timestamp": 1605887258
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The other thing that springs to mind is the <em>yo</em> kana, to be spammed every time anyone uses the Yoneda lemma</p>",
        "id": 217418093,
        "sender_full_name": "Jules Hedges",
        "timestamp": 1605887404
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I approve this message. Do we have any control over what's \"popular\", btw, or is that based on some hidden stats?</p>",
        "id": 217421538,
        "sender_full_name": "[Mod] Morgan Rogers",
        "timestamp": 1605888679
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"275901\">Jules Hedges</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/229122-general.3A-meta/topic/custom.20emojis/near/217418093\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The other thing that springs to mind is the <em>yo</em> kana, to be spammed every time anyone uses the Yoneda lemma</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Actually I'm quite angry that the yo kana cannot be easily used in <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mtext>LaTeX</mtext></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\LaTeX</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.89883em;vertical-align:-0.2155em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord textrm\">L</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.36em;\"></span><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.68333em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.904999em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord textrm mtight sizing reset-size6 size3\">A</span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord textrm\">T</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.46782999999999997em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.7845em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord textrm\">E</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2155em;\"><span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.125em;\"></span><span class=\"mord textrm\">X</span></span></span></span></span></span> here. I still do believe that it should be the common notation for the Yoneda embedding.</p>",
        "id": 217421760,
        "sender_full_name": "Fabrizio Genovese",
        "timestamp": 1605888765
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This is almost certainly LaTeX's fault rather then Zulip's fault..... last year I wanted to use Cyrillic sha as a symbol, and it was incredibly difficult</p>",
        "id": 217422065,
        "sender_full_name": "Jules Hedges",
        "timestamp": 1605888891
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And that was in a document that I had full control over</p>",
        "id": 217422112,
        "sender_full_name": "Jules Hedges",
        "timestamp": 1605888913
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Well, yes and no. The problem is that we cannot, basically, load our packages and macro in the organization settings</p>",
        "id": 217422152,
        "sender_full_name": "Fabrizio Genovese",
        "timestamp": 1605888930
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Packages, I can undestand why. But the obvious solution would be having the LaTeX plugin to run on a full tex distribution.</p>",
        "id": 217422262,
        "sender_full_name": "Fabrizio Genovese",
        "timestamp": 1605888968
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Macros, I really don't. In principle any user could define their own macro file. They could get replaced by substitution.</p>",
        "id": 217422326,
        "sender_full_name": "Fabrizio Genovese",
        "timestamp": 1605888999
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So, for instance, if in my macro file I have <code>\\newcommand{CategoryC}{\\mathcal{C}}</code> then <code>\\CategoryC</code> is replaced by <code>\\mathcal{C}</code> every time I use it in a <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mtext>LaTeX</mtext></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\LaTeX</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.89883em;vertical-align:-0.2155em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord textrm\">L</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.36em;\"></span><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.68333em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.904999em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord textrm mtight sizing reset-size6 size3\">A</span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord textrm\">T</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.46782999999999997em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.7845em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord textrm\">E</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2155em;\"><span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.125em;\"></span><span class=\"mord textrm\">X</span></span></span></span></span></span> environment.</p>",
        "id": 217422456,
        "sender_full_name": "Fabrizio Genovese",
        "timestamp": 1605889049
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Notice that this macro file could be absolutely meta, you don't need to directly feed with <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mtext>LaTeX</mtext></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\LaTeX</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.89883em;vertical-align:-0.2155em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord textrm\">L</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.36em;\"></span><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.68333em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.904999em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord textrm mtight sizing reset-size6 size3\">A</span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord textrm\">T</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.46782999999999997em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.7845em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord textrm\">E</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2155em;\"><span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.125em;\"></span><span class=\"mord textrm\">X</span></span></span></span></span></span> to make it work <span aria-label=\"smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f642\" role=\"img\" title=\"smile\">:smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 217422515,
        "sender_full_name": "Fabrizio Genovese",
        "timestamp": 1605889072
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(Notice that this would immediately enable Tikz diagrams and all sort of things, so we'd have a way to decently express ourselves as one would believe we should, given that it's the 21st century we live in...)</p>",
        "id": 217422742,
        "sender_full_name": "Fabrizio Genovese",
        "timestamp": 1605889159
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Testing <img alt=\":yo:\" class=\"emoji\" src=\"https://zulip-avatars.s3.amazonaws.com/21317/emoji/images/19121.png\" title=\"yo\"></p>",
        "id": 217423329,
        "sender_full_name": "Jules Hedges",
        "timestamp": 1605889405
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Not bad, but black on gray is not the best (I'm using dark mode). Maybe having a colored background instead of a transparent one?</p>",
        "id": 217423580,
        "sender_full_name": "Fabrizio Genovese",
        "timestamp": 1605889517
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>DisCoCat <img alt=\":discocat:\" class=\"emoji\" src=\"https://zulip-avatars.s3.amazonaws.com/21317/emoji/images/19122.jpg\" title=\"discocat\"> ...... the challenge is, it's going to be <em>really hard</em> to find images that look like anything at all when scaled down that small</p>",
        "id": 217423614,
        "sender_full_name": "Jules Hedges",
        "timestamp": 1605889534
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ye, discocat doesn't really show up <span aria-label=\"frown\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f641\" role=\"img\" title=\"frown\">:frown:</span></p>",
        "id": 217423714,
        "sender_full_name": "Fabrizio Genovese",
        "timestamp": 1605889570
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Testing again <img alt=\":yo:\" class=\"emoji\" src=\"https://zulip-avatars.s3.amazonaws.com/21317/emoji/images/19123.png\" title=\"yo\"></p>",
        "id": 217423779,
        "sender_full_name": "Jules Hedges",
        "timestamp": 1605889605
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Nothing changed for me</p>",
        "id": 217423810,
        "sender_full_name": "Fabrizio Genovese",
        "timestamp": 1605889621
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Damn</p>",
        "id": 217423815,
        "sender_full_name": "Jules Hedges",
        "timestamp": 1605889624
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Lel</p>",
        "id": 217423824,
        "sender_full_name": "Fabrizio Genovese",
        "timestamp": 1605889628
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Hm, maybe I'll deal with this later or leave it to whoever gets there first</p>",
        "id": 217424010,
        "sender_full_name": "Jules Hedges",
        "timestamp": 1605889697
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In the meantime, everyone rack your brains for good things to use that will be clear when scaled down to really small</p>",
        "id": 217424052,
        "sender_full_name": "Jules Hedges",
        "timestamp": 1605889717
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Maybe a walnut? <span aria-label=\"smiling face\" class=\"emoji emoji-263a\" role=\"img\" title=\"smiling face\">:smiling_face:</span></p>",
        "id": 217424496,
        "sender_full_name": "[Mod] Morgan Rogers",
        "timestamp": 1605889877
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Woa, that's deep <span aria-label=\"grinning\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f600\" role=\"img\" title=\"grinning\">:grinning:</span></p>",
        "id": 217424676,
        "sender_full_name": "Fabrizio Genovese",
        "timestamp": 1605889943
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In light mode <img alt=\":yo:\" class=\"emoji\" src=\"https://zulip-avatars.s3.amazonaws.com/21317/emoji/images/19123.png\" title=\"yo\"> works great</p>",
        "id": 217427802,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci",
        "timestamp": 1605891086
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Waddaya think <img alt=\":discocat:\" class=\"emoji\" src=\"https://zulip-avatars.s3.amazonaws.com/21317/emoji/images/19127.jpg\" title=\"discocat\"> ?</p>",
        "id": 217428083,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci",
        "timestamp": 1605891195
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Could <img alt=\":yo:\" class=\"emoji\" src=\"https://zulip-avatars.s3.amazonaws.com/21317/emoji/images/19123.png\" title=\"yo\"> have a white outline to make it glow in the dark mode?  (Pun not intended until I saw it, but then totally intended)</p>",
        "id": 217428174,
        "sender_full_name": "Jason Erbele",
        "timestamp": 1605891235
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We've got Obi-Wan Kegrothendieck <img alt=\":grothendieck:\" class=\"emoji\" src=\"https://zulip-avatars.s3.amazonaws.com/21317/emoji/images/19128.jpg\" title=\"grothendieck\"></p>",
        "id": 217428615,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci",
        "timestamp": 1605891398
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Quite disappointing</p>",
        "id": 217428621,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci",
        "timestamp": 1605891403
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This is really hard</p>",
        "id": 217428867,
        "sender_full_name": "Jules Hedges",
        "timestamp": 1605891515
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"309257\">Jason Erbele</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/229122-general.3A-meta/topic/custom.20emojis/near/217428174\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Could <img alt=\":yo:\" class=\"emoji\" src=\"https://zulip-avatars.s3.amazonaws.com/21317/emoji/images/19123.png\" title=\"yo\"> have a white outline to make it glow in the dark mode?  (Pun not intended until I saw it, but then totally intended)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Like this? <img alt=\":darkyo:\" class=\"emoji\" src=\"https://zulip-avatars.s3.amazonaws.com/21317/emoji/images/19129.png\" title=\"darkyo\"></p>",
        "id": 217429162,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci",
        "timestamp": 1605891648
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Testing <code>:zx:</code> <img alt=\":zx:\" class=\"emoji\" src=\"https://zulip-avatars.s3.amazonaws.com/21317/emoji/images/19130.png\" title=\"zx\"></p>",
        "id": 217429508,
        "sender_full_name": "Jules Hedges",
        "timestamp": 1605891787
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Bah, it's so small the colours become invisible</p>",
        "id": 217429537,
        "sender_full_name": "Jules Hedges",
        "timestamp": 1605891796
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Introducing... Grothenwoke <img alt=\":grothenwoke:\" class=\"emoji\" src=\"https://zulip-avatars.s3.amazonaws.com/21317/emoji/images/19137.png\" title=\"grothenwoke\"></p>",
        "id": 217466711,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci",
        "timestamp": 1605911210
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's so small I can't really tell what it looks like</p>",
        "id": 217504287,
        "sender_full_name": "Jules Hedges",
        "timestamp": 1605969389
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It looks more like Grothendieck than the previous one <span aria-label=\"joy\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f602\" role=\"img\" title=\"joy\">:joy:</span></p>",
        "id": 217504593,
        "sender_full_name": "[Mod] Morgan Rogers",
        "timestamp": 1605969985
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm slightly concerned that using people's likeness in emoji could be taken as disrespectful. It may be more judicious to stick to emoji that don't depict real people.</p>",
        "id": 217504729,
        "sender_full_name": "Nathanael Arkor",
        "timestamp": 1605970252
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"276092\">Nathanael Arkor</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/229122-general.3A-meta/topic/custom.20emojis/near/217504729\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I'm slightly concerned that using people's likeness in emoji could be taken as disrespectful. It may be more judicious to stick to emoji that don't depict real people.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Taken as such by whom, for what reason? I don't personally have a stake in <img alt=\":grothendieck:\" class=\"emoji\" src=\"https://zulip-avatars.s3.amazonaws.com/21317/emoji/images/19128.jpg\" title=\"grothendieck\"> but preventing a small amount of fun and expressiveness because someone might some day be upset doesn't seem judicious to me.</p>",
        "id": 217505893,
        "sender_full_name": "Shea Levy",
        "timestamp": 1605972260
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'd propose to not go overboard, and definitely not to use images of anyone who's alive (no Lawvere!). Grothendieck is already heavily memed, this is an established thing</p>",
        "id": 217506578,
        "sender_full_name": "Jules Hedges",
        "timestamp": 1605973539
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I embrace <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"275901\">@Jules Hedges</span>'s point of view on this issue. I explictly avoided Lawvere's emojis for this reason.<br>\nPersonally, I consider being emojified a form of flattering, but I understand other people may not share the same attitude.</p>",
        "id": 217507678,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci",
        "timestamp": 1605975296
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Idk, maybe the elders among us have a different perspective on the issue, if they want to raise a flag I'll certainly listen.<br>\nAll in all, custom emojis are definitely not a hill I'd want to die on , so I'd rather remove them than cause any trouble</p>",
        "id": 217507763,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci",
        "timestamp": 1605975479
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Lawvere would probably be annoyed by being used as an emoji.  He'd probably be annoyed by almost everything we say here.</p>",
        "id": 217509976,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1605978834
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I did have an .... interesting conversation the one time I met him.</p>",
        "id": 217588907,
        "sender_full_name": "David Michael Roberts",
        "timestamp": 1606106229
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Very interested to know why よ was made into an emoji. What was the particular reason?</p>",
        "id": 217667656,
        "sender_full_name": "Pedro Minicz",
        "timestamp": 1606157624
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I see the discussion about light/dark mode above, but fail to see why よ in the first place (the only thing that comes to mind is the よneda lemma).</p>",
        "id": 217667803,
        "sender_full_name": "Pedro Minicz",
        "timestamp": 1606157678
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Some people use <img alt=\":darkyo:\" class=\"emoji\" src=\"https://zulip-avatars.s3.amazonaws.com/21317/emoji/images/19129.png\" title=\"darkyo\"> to denote the Yoneda embedding, so it's handy to have it</p>",
        "id": 217668181,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci",
        "timestamp": 1606157867
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I suppose よ was made into an emoji in response to the mention at the start of this thread that it would be nice to use よ as a reaction emoji whenever anyone invoked the Yoneda Lemma.   Presumably it was also considered briefly as a way to include よ as the name of the Yoneda embedding, before <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"276071\">@Nathaniel Virgo</span> showed how the actual よ character could be used directly in Zulip's version of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mtext>LaTeX</mtext></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\LaTeX</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.89883em;vertical-align:-0.2155em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord textrm\">L</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.36em;\"></span><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.68333em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.904999em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord textrm mtight sizing reset-size6 size3\">A</span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord textrm\">T</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.46782999999999997em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.7845em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord textrm\">E</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2155em;\"><span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.125em;\"></span><span class=\"mord textrm\">X</span></span></span></span></span></span>.</p>",
        "id": 217675489,
        "sender_full_name": "Jason Erbele",
        "timestamp": 1606161419
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Well, i wrote that post and then it was the first one I added</p>",
        "id": 217675665,
        "sender_full_name": "Jules Hedges",
        "timestamp": 1606161496
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>David: I've had quite a few interesting conversations with him. And I don't say that ironically.</p>",
